WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.600
So, I'm going to talk about the Phase I first-in-human dose escalation results from the TRIGNITE-1

00:00:08.600 --> 00:00:19.580
study evaluating ISB2001, and this was initially presented at ASCO 2025, this data.

00:00:19.580 --> 00:00:28.640
So key characteristics of ISB2001, this is a BCMA, CD38, and CD3 tri-specific antibody

00:00:28.640 --> 00:00:36.940
with higher affinity targeting of BCMA and CD38 to enhance civility to myeloma cells

00:00:36.940 --> 00:00:43.840
and lower affinity binding to CD3 with the goal of minimizing off-tumor toxicity and

00:00:43.840 --> 00:00:48.800
T-cell exhaustion.

00:00:48.800 --> 00:00:56.340
The dose escalation portion of this study evaluated 9 dose levels going up to 2700 micrograms

00:00:56.340 --> 00:00:57.720
per kilogram.

00:00:57.720 --> 00:00:58.620
Okay.

00:00:58.620 --> 00:01:05.820
Key eligibility for this study included patients with 3+ prior lines of therapy who were triple

00:01:05.820 --> 00:01:08.380
class exposed.

00:01:08.380 --> 00:01:14.620
Prior CAR-T and/or Bispecific therapy was allowed, with the washout required to

00:01:14.620 --> 00:01:19.800
be 3 months for CAR-T and 28 days for prior Bispecific therapy.

00:01:19.800 --> 00:01:28.600
ISB2001 was administered as a subcutaneous injection once weekly following initial step-up doses.

00:01:28.620 --> 00:01:36.520
And data presented here is from the dose escalation portion of the study for the initial 35 patients

00:01:36.520 --> 00:01:40.040
who had at least 1 month of follow-up at the time of data cut-off.

00:01:40.040 --> 00:01:47.040
The median follow-up for these patients was 6.3 months.

00:01:47.040 --> 00:01:55.500
Baseline characteristics, the median number of prior lines of therapy was 6, 49% of patients

00:01:55.500 --> 00:01:58.600
were triple class refractory.

00:01:58.600 --> 00:02:05.640
And um, 46% of patients had prior exposure to BCMA-directed therapy, including 7 patients

00:02:05.640 --> 00:02:13.440
with prior BCMA bispecifics, 7 patients with prior BCMA antibody drug conjugate, and 4 patients

00:02:13.440 --> 00:02:16.340
with prior BCMA-directed CAR-T therapy.

00:02:16.340 --> 00:02:21.600
Extramedullary disease was present in 34% of patients at screening, and 40% of patients

00:02:21.600 --> 00:02:28.580
had high-risk cytogenetics.

00:02:28.580 --> 00:02:32.240
ISB2001 was associated with a manageable safety profile.

00:02:32.240 --> 00:02:36.920
There were no DLTs observed across the full dose escalation.

00:02:36.920 --> 00:02:45.100
CRS events were mostly low-grade, with 57% grade 1 CRS and 11% grade 2 CRS.

00:02:45.100 --> 00:02:49.820
And this mostly occurred after the first step-up dose, with a median time to onset of 2 days

00:02:49.820 --> 00:02:52.080
and median duration of 2 days.

00:02:52.080 --> 00:02:58.560
13 patients received tocilizumab for CS, and there was no prophylactic tocilizumab administered.

00:02:58.560 --> 00:03:03.880
One patient developed grade 1 ICANS, but there were no other drug-related neurologic

00:03:03.880 --> 00:03:05.780
AEs.

00:03:05.780 --> 00:03:10.180
There was one grade 5 cardiac arrest that was deemed not related to study treatment.

00:03:10.180 --> 00:03:14.080
This was in a patient with significant cardiovascular history.

00:03:14.080 --> 00:03:20.120
And then in terms of hematologic toxicity, grade 3 or higher neutropenia and thrombocytopenia

00:03:20.120 --> 00:03:27.220
were seen in 43% and 23% of patients respectively, and 14% of patients had grade 3 or higher

00:03:27.220 --> 00:03:28.540
anemia.

00:03:28.540 --> 00:03:35.740
And in other patients, grade 3 or higher occurred in 29% of patients.

00:03:35.740 --> 00:03:40.820
Responses were observed starting at dose level 3, with an overall response rate among all

00:03:40.820 --> 00:03:48.180
patients in this cohort of 74%, but among patients treated with effective dose levels,

00:03:48.180 --> 00:03:58.520
the response rate overall was 79%, with a 30% rate of CR or better.

00:03:58.520 --> 00:04:02.440
This month, estimated duration of response was 90%.

00:04:02.440 --> 00:04:09.620
And among 10 patients who had at least a CR, 8 of those were MRD-evaluable, and the rate

00:04:09.620 --> 00:04:14.840
of MRD negativity by clonoseq was 75%.

00:04:14.840 --> 00:04:25.640
Importantly, we also saw high responses among difficult-to-treat patient subgroups, so response

00:04:25.640 --> 00:04:28.500
rates overall between 70% to 75%.

00:04:28.500 --> 00:04:33.540
Among patients who had failed prior CAR-T or Bispecific therapy, patients who

00:04:33.540 --> 00:04:40.300
had failed prior BCMA therapies, and patients who were refractory to CD38-directed therapies.

00:04:40.300 --> 00:04:46.080
Additionally, the rate of response among patients with extramedullary disease at baseline

00:04:46.080 --> 00:04:56.780
was 82%, and patients with high-risk cytogenetics, the overall response rate was 78%.

00:04:56.780 --> 00:04:58.480
Pharmakinetic data was also encouraging.

00:04:58.480 --> 00:05:11.280
With a dose-proportional PK profile and a median half-life of 17 days, supporting the evaluation of less frequent dosing intervals in dose expansion.

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:26.040
We also saw rapid reductions in soluble BCMA levels, as well as rapid increases in T-cell proliferation, even among patients who had received prior CAR-T and or Bispecific therapies.

00:05:28.460 --> 00:05:41.180
So, ISB2001 demonstrates proof of concept for dual targeting of BCMA and CD38 and provides

00:05:41.180 --> 00:05:47.780
early evidence that such an approach may help to overcome relapses driven by tumor heterogeneity

00:05:47.780 --> 00:05:50.900
and antigen escape.

00:05:50.900 --> 00:05:56.900
Efficacy also appears notable despite prior BCMA-directed therapy and prior T-cell redirecting

00:05:56.900 --> 00:06:00.060
therapy exposure in many patients.

00:06:00.060 --> 00:06:08.320
So, in conclusion, dose escalation was completed with no DLTs observed up to a dose of 2,700

00:06:08.320 --> 00:06:10.720
micrograms per kilogram.

00:06:10.720 --> 00:06:14.600
This drug was associated with a manageable safety profile with predominantly low-grade

00:06:14.600 --> 00:06:20.420
CRS and minimal neurotoxicity, and we saw deep and durable responses at active doses

00:06:20.420 --> 00:06:25.340
with an overall response rate of 79 percent, a CR or better rate of 60 percent.

00:06:25.340 --> 00:06:32.940
And among evaluable patients, an MRD negativity rate of 75 percent, with a median duration

00:06:32.940 --> 00:06:36.140
of response not reached.

00:06:36.140 --> 00:06:42.160
We also saw robust activity across key subgroups, with efficacy seen regardless of prior CAR-T

00:06:42.160 --> 00:06:49.020
exposure, T-cell engagers, and BCMA-directed therapies and CD38 refractoriness.

00:06:49.020 --> 00:06:54.240
Dose expansion is ongoing to define the recommended phase 2 dose and future dosing strategies.

00:06:54.240 --> 00:06:55.240
Thank you.

00:06:55.340 --> 00:06:56.180
I'm sorry.
